{{Not|以心電信}}
'''以心傳心'''（{{jpn|kn=以心伝心|rm=Ishin-denshin}}）是一個[[日本|日本]][[熟语|熟语]]<ref name=Maynard-1993>{{cite book| last1=Maynard| first1=Michael L| last2=Maynard| first2=Senko K| author3=Taki| title=101 Japanese Idioms: Understanding Japanese Language and Culture Through Popular Phrases| url=https://archive.org/details/listenlearnjapan00mayn|year=1993| publisher=McGraw Hill Professional| isbn=978-0-8442-8496-5| page=[https://archive.org/details/listenlearnjapan00mayn/page/n65 113]}}</ref>，意指不用說出來也能[[理解|理解]]對方意思的[[人際溝通|溝通方式]]<ref name="Cheung1993">{{cite book|last=Cheung|first=King-Kok|title=Articulate Silences: Hisaye Yamamoto, Maxine Hong Kingston, Joy Kogawa|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Z0DrUokTlmgC&pg=PA146|access-date=2012-07-29|year=1993|publisher=Cornell University Press|isbn=978-0-8014-8147-5|page=146|archive-date=2014-01-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140102045121/http://books.google.com/books?id=Z0DrUokTlmgC&pg=PA146}}</ref>。

儘管[[普世文化通則|普世人類皆懂得]]理解沉默背後的意思，但一些日本人相信這是[[日本文化|日本文化]]的獨有特徵<ref name="DaviesIkeno2002">{{cite book|last1=Davies|first1=Roger J.|last2=Ikeno|first2=Osamu|title=The Japanese Mind: Understanding Contemporary Japanese Culture|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=TW7lHYwXhS4C&pg=PA105|access-date=2012-07-28|date=2002-03-15|publisher=Tuttle Publishing|isbn=978-0-8048-3295-3|pages=52–54, 105|archive-date=2014-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140103130441/http://books.google.com/books?id=TW7lHYwXhS4C&pg=PA105}}</ref>。其跟{{link-en|腹藝|haragei}}在概念上有所不同——前者是指被動地理解對方的內心，後者則指有意進行的非語言溝通。日本人传统上认为「以心傳心」是經由內心或腹部（內部的象徵）進行的無聲交流；他們認為用到嘴部或臉部（外部）的溝通較容易出現不够坦誠的情況<ref name="DaviesIkeno2002"/>。這一概念經由中國傳入日本，並跟[[禅宗|禅宗]]有關。對於禅宗而言，以心傳心即代表直接經由心靈傳法<ref name="DaviesIkeno2002"/><ref name="Baroni2002">{{cite book|last=Baroni|first=Helen Josephine|title=The Illustrated Encyclopedia of Zen Buddhism|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=smNM4ElP3XgC&pg=PA156|access-date=2012-07-28|year=2002|publisher=The Rosen Publishing Group|isbn=978-0-8239-2240-6|page=156|archive-date=2014-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140103133326/http://books.google.com/books?id=smNM4ElP3XgC&pg=PA156}}</ref>。[[禅宗|禅宗]]把[[释迦牟尼|释迦牟尼]]跟[[摩訶迦葉|摩訶迦葉]]傳法的一幕形容為「以心傳心」<ref name="Shores1998">{{cite web |url=http://terebess.hu/zen/mesterek/JeffShore.pdf |title=THE SOURCE OF ZEN: WHO TRANSMITS WHAT? |last1=Shore |first1=Jeff |date=1998 |access-date=2021-02-24 |archive-date=2017-02-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170215181838/http://terebess.hu/zen/mesterek/JeffShore.pdf }}</ref><ref name="Durix1991">{{cite book |last=Durix |first=Claude |date=1991 |title=Cent Clés pour Comprendre le Zen |url=https://archive.org/details/centclespourcomp0000duri |publisher=Le Courrier du Livre |page=[https://archive.org/details/centclespourcomp0000duri/page/43 43] |isbn=978-2-7029-0261-5}}</ref>。

以心傳心等非語言溝通方式繼續影響當代的日本文化和[[伦理学|伦理]]觀念<ref name="Murata-2010">{{cite book| last=Murata| first=K| editor=Morais da Costa| editor2=Jorge Goncalo| title=Ethical Issues and Social Dilemmas in Knowledge Management: Organizational Innovation: Organizational Innovation| chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KB1IDmxDEpkC&pg=PA10| year=2010| publisher=IGI Global| isbn=978-1-61520-874-6| page=10| chapter=Knowledge Creation and Sharing in Japanese Organisations: A Socio-Cultural Perspective on ba| access-date=2021-02-24| archive-date=2018-09-16| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180916103914/https://books.google.com/books?id=KB1IDmxDEpkC&pg=PA10}}</ref>——從[[商业伦理|商业伦理]]<ref name=Dougherty-1991>{{cite book| last=Dougherty| first=Andrew J |title=Japan: 2000| year=1991| publisher=Rochester Institute of Technology| page=17}}</ref>到临终关怀，無一不受其影響<ref name="Slingsby2005">{{Cite journal| last =Slingsby  | first =Brian Taylor  | title = The nature of relative subjectivity: a reflexive mode of thought | url =https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-medicine-and-philosophy_2005-02_30_1/page/9  | journal=The Journal of Medicine and Philosophy  |volume= 30|issue=1 |pages=9–25| year =2005  | pmid =15814365 |doi=10.1080/03605310590907039 }}</ref>。

